s with GoDoc | Clear purpose documented | 0.5h |\n359: | 4.22.3 | Document all exported methods with GoDoc | Parameters and return values documented | 0.5h |\n360: | 4.22.4 | Add execution flow documentation | Pending→Running→Completed diagram | 0.5h |\n361: | 4.22.5 | Document environment variables | PICOD_* variables listed | 0.5h |\n362: | 4.22.6 | Add usage examples in code comments | Example code in godoc | 0.5h |\n363: \n364: **Deliverable:** Code is well-documented for future maintainers.\n365: \n366: ---\n367: \n368: ## Summary\n369: \n370: | Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n371: |-------|-------|------------|\n372: | ST-4.1: Type Definitions | 10 | 5h |\n373: | ST-4.2: Error Definitions | 13 | 3h |\n374: | ST-4.3: Request Validation | 8 | 4h |\n375: | ST-4.4: Executor Structure | 7 | 4h |\n376: | ST-4.5: Sync Execution | 11 | 6h |\n377: | ST-4.6: Async Execution | 7 | 3.5h |\n378: | ST-4.7: Status Management | 9 | 4.5h |\n379: | ST-4.8: Cancellation | 6 | 3h |\n380: | ST-4.9: Output Streaming | 10 | 5h |\n381: | ST-4.10: Sandbox Integration | 8 | 4h |\n382: | ST-4.11: Store Integration | 4 | 2h |\n383: | ST-4.12: Unit Tests (Types) | 4 | 2h |\n384: | ST-4.13: Unit Tests (Validation) | 7 | 3.5h |\n385: | ST-4.14: Unit Tests (Execute) | 8 | 4h |\n386: | ST-4.15: Unit Tests (ExecuteAsync) | 5 | 3h |\n387: | ST-4.16: Unit Tests (GetStatus) | 6 | 3h |\n388: | ST-4.17: Unit Tests (Cancel) | 5 | 2.5h |\n389: | ST-4.18: Unit Tests (StreamOutput) | 5 | 3h |\n390: | ST-4.19: Unit Tests (Errors) | 3 | 1.5h |\n391: | ST-4.20: Integration Tests | 8 | 7h |\n392: | ST-4.21: Mock Implementations | 3 | 2.5h |\n393: | ST-4.22: Documentation | 6 | 3h |\n394: | **Total** | **153** | **73h** |\n395: \n396: ---\n397: \n398: ## File Deliverables Checklist\n399: \n400: - [ ] `pkg/picod/types.go` — Type definitions\n401: - [ ] `pkg/picod/errors.go` — Error type definitions\n402: - [ ] `pkg/picod/validation.go` — Request validation\n403: - [ ] `pkg/picod/executor.go` — CommandExecutor implementation\n404: - [ ] `pkg/picod/output.go` — Output capture and streaming\n405: - [ ] `pkg/picod/sandbox_client.go` — Sandbox integration\n406: - [ ] `pkg/picod/status.go` — Status management\n407: - [ ] `pkg/picod/executor_test.go` — Unit tests\n408: - [ ] `pkg/picod/executor_integration_test.go` — Integration tests\n409: - [ ] `pkg/picod/mock_sandbox.go` — Mock sandbox client\n410: - [ ] `pkg/picod/mock_store.go` — Mock store\n411: \n412: ---\n413: \n414: ## Verification Commands\n415: \n416: ```bash\n417: # Build verification\n418: go build ./pkg/picod/...\n419: \n420: # Unit test verification (all picod tests)\n421: go test ./pkg/picod/... -v\n422: \n423: # Specific test suites\n424: go test ./pkg/picod/... -run TestExecute -v\n425: go test ./pkg/picod/... -run TestExecuteAsync -v\n426: go test ./pkg/picod/... -run TestGetStatus -v\n427: go test ./pkg/picod/... -run TestCancel -v\n428: go test ./pkg/picod/... -run TestStreamOutput -v\n429: go test ./pkg/picod/... -run TestValidation -v\n430: \n431: # Race detection\n432: go test ./pkg/picod/... -race\n433: \n434: # Coverage report\n435: go test ./pkg/picod/... -cover\n436: \n437: # Integration tests (requires Docker/sandbox)\n438: go test ./pkg/picod/... -tags=integration -v\n439: ```\n440: \n441: ---\n442: \n443: ## Definition of Done\n444: \n445: - [ ] All 153 tasks complete\n446: - [ ] `CommandExecutor` interface fully implemented\n447: - [ ] All validation rules implemented with tests\n448: - [ ] Unit tests pass (>85% coverage for core files)\n449: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real sandbox and store\n450: - [ ] Race detector clean\n451: - [ ] `go build ./pkg/picod/...` succeeds\n452: - [ ] Documentation complete with GoDoc\n453: - [ ] Mock implementations provided for unit testing\n454: \n455: ---\n456: \n457: ## Dependencies\n458: \n459: | Dependency | Purpose |\n460: |------------|---------|\n461: | AR-009: Sandbox Interface | Command execution in sandboxes |\n462: | AR-012: Store Interface | Status persistence |\n463: | AR-013: Redis Implementation | Store backend option |\n464: | AR-014: Valkey Implementation | Store backend option |\n465: | `github.com/google/uuid` | ExecutionID generation |\n466: | `pkg/common/types` | Shared types |\n467: \n468: ---\n469: \n470: ## Design Notes\n471: \n472: - **Execution ID format:** `[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+`, 8-64 characters\n473: - **State machine:** pending → running → completed | failed | cancelled\n474: - **Terminal states:** completed, failed, cancelled (immutable)\n475: - **Output buffering:** Circular buffer with configurable size\n476: - **Concurrency:** Semaphore-based limit enforcement\n477: - **Timeout:** Context-based with cancellation propagation\n478: - **Sandbox integration:** Via AR-009 interface\n479: - **Store integration:** Via AR-012 interface\n480: - **Environment config:** PICOD_* variables\n\n(End of file - total 480 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API (PicoD Command Execution API)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n> **Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-015 implements the PicoD command execution API providing synchronous and asynchronous command execution in sandbox environments. The API supports resource constraints, output streaming, execution cancellation, and persistent status tracking.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Type Definitions and Interfaces\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775875769466,"end":1775875769496}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875769500,"sessionID":"ses_2858ed25cfferLpNnlnb8fp241","part":{"id":"prt_d7a71b743001zk4qp8N3Fz50wU","messageID":"msg_d7a7180630013FDxAZbbMrmfKt","sessionID":"ses_2858ed25cfferLpNnlnb8fp241","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/picod/doc.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/picod/doc.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: // Package picod provides the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n18: //\n19: // PicoD (Pico Daemon) is a lightweight command execution service that enables\n20: // secure, sandboxed command execution within agent sessions. It provides:\n21: //\n22: //   - Synchronous and asynchronous command execution\n23: //   - Resource constraint enforcement (CPU, memory, I/O)\n24: //   - Output capture and streaming\n25: //   - Execution lifecycle management (pending, running, completed, failed, cancelled)\n26: //   - Timeout and cancellation support\n27: //\n28: // The primary interface is CommandExecutor, which provides methods for executing\n29: // commands and managing their lifecycle:\n30: //\n31: //\texecutor := picod.NewExecutor(config, store, resolver)\n32: //\tresult, err := executor.Execute(ctx, ExecutionRequest{\n33: //\t    Command:   \"echo\",\n34: //\t    Args:      []string{\"hello\"},\n35: //\t    SessionID: \"sess-abc123\",\n36: //\t})\n37: //\n38: // Error handling uses sentinel errors for specific conditions:\n39: //   - ErrInvalidRequest: Malformed execution request\n40: //   - ErrInvalidCommand: Empty or invalid command\n41: //   - ErrTimeout: Execution exceeded timeout\n42: //   - ErrSandboxUnavailable: Sandbox not accessible\n43: //   - ErrExecutionNotFound: Execution ID not found\n44: //\n45: // For more information, see the AR-015 design document.\n46: package picod\n\n(End of file - total 46 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\n// Package picod provides the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n//\n// PicoD (Pico Daemon) is a lightweight command execution service that enables\n// secure, sandboxed command execution within agent sessions. It provides:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/picod/doc.go","time":{"start":1775875769470,"end":1775875769499}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875769503,"sessionID":"ses_2858ed25cfferLpNnlnb8fp241","part":{"id":"prt_d7a71af66001Z6kJ1R1RcgTdtK","messageID":"msg_d7a7180630013FDxAZbbMrmfKt","sessionID":"ses_2858ed25cfferLpNnlnb8fp241","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/picod/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/picod/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package picod\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \t\"context\"\n21: \t\"fmt\"\n22: \t\"strings\"\n23: \t\"time\"\n24: \n25: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n26: )\n27: \n28: // ExecutionID uniquely identifies a command execution.\n29: type ExecutionID string\n30: \n31: // ExecutionState represents the state of command execution.\n32: type ExecutionState string\n33: \n34: const (\n35: \t// StatePending indicates the execution is queued\n36: \tStatePending ExecutionState = \"pending\"\n37: \n38: \t// StateRunning indicates the execution is in progress\n39: \tStateRunning ExecutionState = \"running\"\n40: \n41: \t// StateCompleted indicates the execution completed successfully\n42: \tStateCompleted ExecutionState = \"completed\"\n43: \n44: \t// StateFailed indicates the execution failed\n45: \tStateFailed ExecutionState = \"failed\"\n46: \n47: \t// StateCancelled indicates the execution was cancelled\n48: \tStateCancelled ExecutionState = \"cancelled\"\n49: )\n50: \n51: // IsTerminal returns true if the state is terminal (completed, failed, or cancelled).\n52: func (s ExecutionState) IsTerminal() bool {\n53: \treturn s == StateCompleted || s == StateFailed || s == StateCancelled\n54: }\n55: \n56: // String returns the string representation of the state.\n57: func (s ExecutionState) String() string {\n58: \treturn string(s)\n59: }\n60: \n61: // ExecutionRequest contains parameters for command execution.\n62: type ExecutionRequest struct {\n63: \t// Command is the command to execute (required)\n64: \tCommand string `json:\"command\"`\n65: \n66: \t// Args are the command arguments\n67: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n68: \n69: \t// WorkingDir is the working directory for execution (default: sandbox default)\n70: \tWorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n71: \n72: \t// Environment defines environment variables (merged with sandbox defaults)\n73: \tEnvironment map[string]string `json:\"environment,omitempty\"`\n74: \n75: \t// Timeout is the maximum execution time (default: 30s)\n76: \tTimeout time.Duration `json:\"timeout,omitempty\"`\n77: \n78: \t// ResourceLimits defines resource constraints for execution\n79: \tResourceLimits ResourceConstraints `json:\"resourceLimits,omitempty\"`\n80: \n81: \t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n82: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n83: }\n84: \n85: // Validate validates the execution request.\n86: func (r *ExecutionRequest) Validate() error {\n87: \tif strings.TrimSpace(r.Command) == \"\" {\n88: \t\treturn ErrInvalidCommand\n89: \t}\n90: \tif strings.Contains(r.Command, \"..\") || strings.Contains(r.Command, \"//\") {\n91: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%w: command contains invalid characters\", ErrInvalidCommand)\n92: \t}\n93: \tif r.SessionID == \"\" {\n94: \t\treturn ErrInvalidSessionID\n95: \t}\n96: \tif r.WorkingDir != \"\" && !isAllowedWorkingDir(r.WorkingDir) {\n97: \t\treturn ErrInvalidWorkingDir\n98: \t}\n99: \tfor name := range r.Environment {\n100: \t\tif !isValidEnvVarName(name) {\n101: \t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%w: invalid environment variable name: %s\", ErrInvalidRequest, name)\n102: \t\t}\n103: \t}\n104: \treturn nil\n105: }\n106: \n107: // ExecutionResult contains the result of a command execution.\n108: type ExecutionResult struct {\n109: \t// ID is the unique execution identifier\n110: \tID ExecutionID `json:\"id\"`\n111: \n112: \t// Status contains the execution status details\n113: \tStatus ExecutionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n114: \n115: \t// ExitCode is the command exit code (0 for success)\n116: \tExitCode int `json:\"exitCode\"`\n117: \n118: \t// Stdout contains the captured standard output\n119: \tStdout []byte `json:\"stdout,omitempty\"`\n120: \n121: \t// Stderr contains the captured standard error\n122: \tStderr []byte `json:\"stderr,omitempty\"`\n123: \n124: \t// StartedAt is when execution started\n125: \tStartedAt time.Time `json:\"startedAt\"`\n126: \n127: \t// FinishedAt is when execution completed\n128: \tFinishedAt time.Time `json:\"finishedAt\"`\n129: \n130: \t// Error contains error details if execution failed\n131: \tError *ExecutionError `json:\"error,omitempty\"`\n132: \n133: \t// Truncated indicates if output was truncated due to size limits\n134: \tTruncated bool `json:\"truncated,omitempty\"`\n135: }\n136: \n137: // ExecutionError contains detailed error information.\n138: type ExecutionError struct {\n139: \t// Code is the machine-readable error code\n140: \tCode string `json:\"code\"`\n141: \n142: \t// Message is the human-readable error message\n143: \tMessage string `json:\"message\"`\n144: \n145: \t// Details contains additional error context\n146: \tDetails map[string]interface{} `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n147: }\n148: \n149: // ExecutionStatus represents the current state of an execution.\n150: type ExecutionStatus struct {\n151: \t// ID is the unique execution identifier\n152: \tID ExecutionID `json:\"id\"`\n153: \n154: \t// State is the current execution state\n155: \tState ExecutionState `json:\"state\"`\n156: \n157: \t// StartedAt is when execution started (nil if not started)\n158: \tStartedAt *time.Time `json:\"startedAt,omitempty\"`\n159: \n160: \t// FinishedAt is when execution completed (nil if not finished)\n161: \tFinishedAt *time.Time `json:\"finishedAt,omitempty\"`\n162: \n163: \t// ExitCode is the command exit code (nil if not finished)\n164: \tExitCode *int `json:\"exitCode,omitempty\"`\n165: \n166: \t// OutputRef references stored output (for large outputs)\n167: \tOutputRef string `json:\"outputRef,omitempty\"`\n168: \n169: \t// SessionID is the target sandbox session ID\n170: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n171: }\n172: \n173: // ResourceConstraints defines resource limits for execution.\n174: type ResourceConstraints struct {\n175: \t// MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes (0 = unlimited)\n176: \tMaxMemory int64 `json:\"maxMemory,omitempty\"`\n177: \n178: \t// MaxCPU is the maximum CPU percentage (0-100, 0 = unlimited)\n179: \tMaxCPU float64 `json:\"maxCpu,omitempty\"`\n180: \n181: \t// MaxIOBytes is the maximum IO bandwidth in bytes per second (0 = unlimited)\n182: \tMaxIOBytes int64 `json:\"maxIoBytes,omitempty\"`\n183: \n184: \t// MaxFiles is the maximum number of open file descriptors (0 = unlimited)\n185: \tMaxFiles int `json:\"maxFiles,omitempty\"`\n186: }\n187: \n188: // IsEmpty returns true if no constraints are set.\n189: func (r ResourceConstraints) IsEmpty() bool {\n190: \treturn r.MaxMemory == 0 && r.MaxCPU == 0 && r.MaxIOBytes == 0 && r.MaxFiles == 0\n191: }\n192: \n193: // Validate validates resource constraints.\n194: func (r ResourceConstraints) Validate() error {\n195: \tif r.MaxMemory < 0 {\n196: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxMemory cannot be negative\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n197: \t}\n198: \tif r.MaxCPU < 0 || r.MaxCPU > 100 {\n199: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxCpu must be between 0 and 100\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n200: \t}\n201: \tif r.MaxIOBytes < 0 {\n202: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxIoBytes cannot be negative\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n203: \t}\n204: \tif r.MaxFiles < 0 {\n205: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxFiles cannot be negative\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n206: \t}\n207: \treturn nil\n208: }\n209: \n210: // OutputChunk represents a piece of output from a command.\n211: type OutputChunk struct {\n212: \t// Data is the output data\n213: \tData []byte `json:\"data\"`\n214: \n215: \t// Type indicates the output source\n216: \tType OutputType `json:\"type\"`\n217: \n218: \t// Timestamp is when the output was captured\n219: \tTimestamp time.Time `json:\"timestamp\"`\n220: }\n221: \n222: // OutputType indicates the source of output.\n223: type OutputType string\n224: \n225: const (\n226: \t// Stdout indicates standard output\n227: \tStdout OutputType = \"stdout\"\n228: \n229: \t// Stderr indicates standard error\n230: \tStderr OutputType = \"stderr\"\n231: )\n232: \n233: // String returns the string representation of the output type.\n234: func (o OutputType) String() string {\n235: \treturn string(o)\n236: }\n237: \n238: // CommandExecutor defines the interface for executing commands in sandboxes.\n239: type CommandExecutor interface {\n240: \t// Execute runs a command synchronously and returns the result.\n241: \t// Blocks until execution completes, times out, or is cancelled.\n242: \tExecute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n243: \n244: \t// ExecuteAsync runs a command asynchronously and returns an execution ID.\n245: \t// Returns immediately; use GetStatus to poll for completion.\n246: \tExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n247: \n248: \t// GetStatus retrieves the current status of an execution.\n249: \t// Returns ErrExecutionNotFound if the execution does not exist.\n250: \tGetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n251: \n252: \t// Cancel stops a running execution.\n253: \t// Returns ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete if execution is in terminal state.\n254: \tCancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n255: \n256: \t// StreamOutput returns a channel for streaming output from an execution.\n257: \t// Channel is closed when execution completes or context is cancelled.\n258: \tStreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n259: }\n260: \n261: // ExecutionStore defines the interface for execution status persistence.\n262: type ExecutionStore interface {\n263: \t// CreateStatus creates a new execution status record.\n264: \tCreateStatus(ctx context.Context, status *ExecutionStatus) error\n265: \n266: \t// GetStatus retrieves execution status by ID.\n267: \t// Returns ErrExecutionNotFound if not found.\n268: \tGetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n269: \n270: \t// UpdateStatus updates execution status.\n271: \tUpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, status *ExecutionStatus) error\n272: \n273: \t// UpdateStatusWithTransition updates status with state transition validation.\n274: \t// Only allows valid state transitions.\n275: \tUpdateStatusWithTransition(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID, from, to ExecutionState, updateFn func(*ExecutionStatus)) error\n276: \n277: \t// DeleteStatus removes an execution status record.\n278: \tDeleteStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n279: \n280: \t// ListExecutions lists executions filtered by state and session.\n281: \tListExecutions(ctx context.Context, filter ExecutionFilter) ([]*ExecutionStatus, error)\n282: \n283: \t// StoreOutput stores execution output for later retrieval.\n284: \tStoreOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID, stdout, stderr []byte) error\n285: \n286: \t// GetOutput retrieves stored execution output.\n287: \tGetOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (stdout, stderr []byte, err error)\n288: }\n289: \n290: // ExecutionFilter defines filters for listing executions.\n291: type ExecutionFilter struct {\n292: \t// SessionID filters by session\n293: \tSessionID string\n294: \n295: \t// State filters by execution state\n296: \tState ExecutionState\n297: \n298: \t// Limit limits the number of results\n299: \tLimit int\n300: }\n301: \n302: // SandboxResolver resolves session IDs to sandbox information.\n303: type SandboxResolver interface {\n304: \t// Resolve returns sandbox info for a session ID.\n305: \t// Returns ErrSandboxUnavailable if session doesn't exist.\n306: \tResolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n307: }\n308: \n309: // SandboxRunner executes commands in a sandbox.\n310: type SandboxRunner interface {\n311: \t// Run executes a command synchronously.\n312: \tRun(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n313: \n314: \t// Start begins async command execution.\n315: \tStart(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, req ExecutionRequest, id ExecutionID) error\n316: \n317: \t// Cancel stops a running command.\n318: \tCancel(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, id ExecutionID) error\n319: }\n320: \n321: // QueuedExecution represents an execution in the queue.\n322: type QueuedExecution struct {\n323: \tID         ExecutionID\n324: \tRequest    ExecutionRequest\n325: \tEnqueuedAt time.Time\n326: }\n327: \n328: // ExecutionQueue manages the async execution queue.\n329: type ExecutionQueue interface {\n330: \t// Enqueue adds an execution request to the queue.\n331: \t// Returns the assigned execution ID.\n332: \tEnqueue(req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n333: \n334: \t// Dequeue retrieves the next pending execution.\n335: \t// Blocks until an execution is available or context is cancelled.\n336: \tDequeue(ctx context.Context) (*QueuedExecution, error)\n337: \n338: \t// GetPosition returns the queue position for an execution.\n339: \tGetPosition(id ExecutionID) (int, error)\n340: \n341: \t// Remove removes an execution from the queue.\n342: \tRemove(id ExecutionID) error\n343: \n344: \t// Size returns the current queue size.\n345: \tSize() int\n346: }\n\n(End of file - total 346 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage picod\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/picod/types.go","time":{"start":1775875769468,"end":1775875769501}}}}
