{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876041894,"sessionID":"ses_2858ed25cfferLpNnlnb8fp241","part":{"id":"prt_d7a71ec86001Nv4lHm0YLXZz7T","messageID":"msg_d7a71c4dd001Q3kpgYgYHoGKXR","sessionID":"ses_2858ed25cfferLpNnlnb8fp241","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md","content":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API (PicoD File Management API)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n> **Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-016 implements the PicoD File Management API providing secure file operations within sandbox environments. The API supports reading, writing, listing, deleting files, directory management, file streaming, batch operations, and directory watching with comprehensive security controls.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — File Type Definitions\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.1.1 | Define `FileType` type and constants (File, Directory, Symlink) | Constants have correct string values | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.2 | Define `FileContent` struct (Data, Size, Truncated, MIMEType) | All fields match delta-spec; JSON tags present | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.3 | Define `FileInfo` struct (Name, Path, Type, Size, CreatedAt, ModifiedAt, AccessedAt, Permissions, IsSymlink, LinkTarget) | All fields match delta-spec | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.4 | Define `DirectoryListing` struct (Path, Entries, TotalCount) | Fields match delta-spec | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.5 | Define `WriteFileRequest` struct (Path, Data, Overwrite, CreateDirs, Permissions) | Types match spec | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.6 | Define `WriteStreamRequest` struct (Path, ExpectedSize, Overwrite, CreateDirs, Permissions) | All fields present | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.7 | Define `ReadOptions` struct (Offset, Limit) | Types match spec (int64) | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.8 | Define `ListOptions` struct (Recursive, Pattern, Offset, Limit) | All config fields present | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.9 | Define `CopyPair` struct (SourcePath, DestPath, Overwrite) | Fields match delta-spec | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.10 | Define `BatchResult` struct (SuccessCount, FailureCount, Failures) | Map type correct | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.11 | Define `FileEventType` type and constants (FileCreated, FileModified, FileDeleted, FileRenamed) | Constants have correct values | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.12 | Define `FileEvent` struct (Type, Path, Info, Timestamp) | All fields present | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.13 | Define `WatchOptions` struct (Recursive, Pattern, EventTypes) | Slice type for EventTypes | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.14 | Define `Watcher` struct with Stop method | Struct has id, sessionID, path, stop fields | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** All file type definitions compile and match delta-spec exactly.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.2 — FileManager Interface Definition\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.2.1 | Define `FileManager` interface | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.2 | Add `ReadFile(ctx, sessionID, path) (*FileContent, error)` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.3 | Add `ReadFileStream(ctx, sessionID, path, opts) (io.ReadCloser, error)` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.4 | Add `WriteFile(ctx, sessionID, req) (*FileInfo, error)` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.5 | Add `WriteFileStream(ctx, sessionID, req, reader) error` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.6 | Add `DeleteFile(ctx, sessionID, path) error` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.7 | Add `ListDirectory(ctx, sessionID, path, opts) (*DirectoryListing, error)` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.8 | Add `Stat(ctx, sessionID, path) (*FileInfo, error)` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.9 | Add `CreateDirectory(ctx, sessionID, path) (*FileInfo, error)` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.10 | Add `RemoveDirectory(ctx, sessionID, path) error` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.11 | Add `Move(ctx, sessionID, sourcePath, destPath) (*FileInfo, error)` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.12 | Add `Copy(ctx, sessionID, sourcePath, destPath) error` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.13 | Add `BatchStat(ctx, sessionID, paths) (map[string]*FileInfo, error)` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.14 | Add `BatchDelete(ctx, sessionID, paths) (*BatchResult, error)` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.15 | Add `BatchCopy(ctx, sessionID, pairs) (*BatchResult, error)` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.16 | Add `WatchDirectory(ctx, sessionID, path, opts) (*Watcher, <-chan FileEvent, error)` method | Signature matches delta-spec | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** FileManager interface compiles and matches delta-spec exactly.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.3 — Error Type Definitions\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.3.1 | Create `pkg/picod/file_errors.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.2 | Define `ErrInvalidPath` error | Error message: \"picod: invalid path\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.3 | Define `ErrFileNotFound` error | Error message: \"picod: file not found\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.4 | Define `ErrDirectoryNotFound` error | Error message: \"picod: directory not found\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.5 | Define `ErrFileExists` error | Error message: \"picod: file already exists\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.6 | Define `ErrDirectoryExists` error | Error message: \"picod: directory already exists\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.7 | Define `ErrFileTooLarge` error | Error message: \"picod: file too large\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.8 | Define `ErrDirectorySizeExceeded` error | Error message: \"picod: directory size exceeded\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.9 | Define `ErrPathNotAllowed` error | Error message: \"picod: path not allowed\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.10 | Define `ErrFileTypeNotAllowed` error | Error message: \"picod: file type not allowed\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.11 | Define `ErrPermissionDenied` error | Error message: \"picod: permission denied\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.12 | Define `ErrSandboxUnavailable` error | Error message: \"picod: sandbox unavailable\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.13 | Define `ErrInvalidFileRequest` error | Error message: \"picod: invalid file request\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.14 | Define `ErrWatcherClosed` error | Error message: \"picod: watcher closed\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.15 | Define error code constants (ErrorCodeInvalidPath, ErrorCodeFileNotFound, etc.) | All 11 codes defined | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** All 14 error types and 11 error codes defined and exportable.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.4 — Configuration Types\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.4.1 | Define `FileManagerConfig` struct (MaxFileSize, MaxDirectorySize, AllowedPaths, BlockedExtensions, AllowedExtensions, FileOpTimeout, EnableFileWatching, MaxWatchers) | All fields present with correct types | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.2 | Implement `DefaultFileManagerConfig()` function | Returns config with defaults: 100MB, 1GB, /workspace,/tmp, 30s, true, 100 | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.3 | Add configuration from environment variables (PICOD_MAX_FILE_SIZE, PICOD_MAX_DIRECTORY_SIZE, PICOD_ALLOWED_PATHS, PICOD_BLOCKED_EXTENSIONS, PICOD_ALLOWED_EXTENSIONS, PICOD_FILE_OP_TIMEOUT, PICOD_ENABLE_FILE_WATCHING, PICOD_MAX_WATCHERS) | All env vars parsed correctly | 1h |\n| 4.4.4 | Add size parsing (e.g., \"100MB\", \"1GB\") | Parses byte sizes with suffixes | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.5 | Add duration parsing for timeout | Parses Go duration strings | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.6 | Add comma-separated list parsing for paths/extensions | Splits and trims correctly | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.7 | Add boolean parsing for EnableFileWatching | Parses \"true\"/\"false\" | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Configuration types and environment loading implemented.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.5 — Path Validation and Security\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.5.1 | Create `pkg/picod/file_validation.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.2 | Implement `ValidatePath(path string, config *FileManagerConfig) error` | Returns nil for valid paths | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.3 | Validate absolute path requirement | Returns ErrInvalidPath for relative paths | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.4 | Implement path traversal detection (../ patterns) | Returns ErrInvalidPath for traversal attempts | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.5 | Implement path normalization | Clean path before validation | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.6 | Validate allowed paths enforcement | Returns ErrPathNotAllowed for paths outside allowed | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.7 | Validate null bytes in paths | Returns ErrInvalidPath for paths with \\x00 | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.8 | Validate empty paths | Returns ErrInvalidPath for empty string | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.9 | Validate path length limits (maxPathLength=4096, maxFilenameLength=255) | Returns ErrInvalidPath for too long paths | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.10 | Implement symlink resolution with sandbox containment | Returns ErrInvalidPath if symlink escapes sandbox | 1h |\n| 4.5.11 | Implement file type validation (extension checks) | Returns ErrFileTypeNotAllowed for blocked types | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.12 | Validate file size before write | Returns ErrFileTooLarge if exceeds limit | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** All validation rules implemented with unit tests.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.6 — FileManager Core Structure\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.6.1 | Create `pkg/picod/file_manager.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.2 | Define `fileManager` struct with dependencies (config, sandboxClient, store, watcherRegistry) | All fields present | 1h |\n| 4.6.3 | Implement `NewFileManager(config FileManagerConfig, sandboxClient SandboxFileClient, store SessionStore) (FileManager, error)` constructor | Returns initialized FileManager | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.4 | Add concurrency control (mutex for watcher registry) | Thread-safe operations | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.5 | Add session resolution helper | Resolves SessionID to sandbox | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** FileManager structure compiles with proper initialization.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.7 — File Read Operations\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.7.1 | Implement `ReadFile(ctx, sessionID, path) (*FileContent, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.2 | Validate path before reading | Invalid path returns error without sandbox call | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.3 | Resolve sandbox by SessionID | Query store for sandbox info | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.4 | Handle sandbox unavailable error | Returns ErrSandboxUnavailable | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.5 | Read file from sandbox | Returns FileContent with data | 1h |\n| 4.7.6 | Handle non-existent file | Returns ErrFileNotFound | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.7 | Handle file size limit on read | Returns ErrFileTooLarge or Truncated=true | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.8 | Detect MIME type | MIMEType field populated | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.9 | Implement `ReadFileStream(ctx, sessionID, path, opts) (io.ReadCloser, error)` | Returns streaming reader | 1h |\n| 4.7.10 | Support range requests (Offset, Limit) | Stream starts at correct offset | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.11 | Handle context cancellation in stream | Stream closes on cancellation | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** ReadFile and ReadFileStream work with all error cases.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.8 — File Write Operations\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.8.1 | Implement `WriteFile(ctx, sessionID, req) (*FileInfo, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.2 | Validate path and request before writing | Invalid request returns error | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.3 | Validate file size before write | Returns ErrFileTooLarge if data exceeds limit | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.4 | Validate file type (extension) before write | Returns ErrFileTypeNotAllowed if blocked | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.5 | Check overwrite permission | Returns ErrFileExists if Overwrite=false and exists | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.6 | Create parent directories if CreateDirs=true | Directories created as needed | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.7 | Write file to sandbox | File created with correct content | 1h |\n| 4.8.8 | Return FileInfo for written file | Info has correct Name, Size, Type | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.9 | Implement `WriteFileStream(ctx, sessionID, req, reader) error` | Streams data from reader | 1h |\n| 4.8.10 | Handle context cancellation during stream | Operation aborts on cancellation | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.11 | Handle ExpectedSize validation | Validates against actual streamed size | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** WriteFile and WriteFileStream work with validation.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.9 — File Delete Operations\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.9.1 | Implement `DeleteFile(ctx, sessionID, path) error` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.2 | Validate path before deleting | Invalid path returns error | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.3 | Resolve sandbox by SessionID | Query store for sandbox info | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.4 | Handle non-existent file | Returns ErrFileNotFound | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.5 | Delete file from sandbox | File removed successfully | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.6 | Handle permission errors | Returns ErrPermissionDenied | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** DeleteFile works correctly.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.10 — Directory Operations\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.10.1 | Implement `ListDirectory(ctx, sessionID, path, opts) (*DirectoryListing, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.2 | Validate path before listing | Invalid path returns error | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.3 | Handle non-existent directory | Returns ErrDirectoryNotFound | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.4 | List directory entries from sandbox | Returns FileInfo for each entry | 1h |\n| 4.10.5 | Support recursive listing | Returns all subdirectories when Recursive=true | 1h |\n| 4.10.6 | Support pattern filtering (glob) | Filters entries by pattern | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.7 | Support pagination (Offset, Limit) | Returns correct slice of entries | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.8 | Implement `CreateDirectory(ctx, sessionID, path) (*FileInfo, error)` | Creates directory in sandbox | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.9 | Handle existing directory | Returns ErrDirectoryExists | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.10 | Create parent directories as needed | Recursive directory creation | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.11 | Implement `RemoveDirectory(ctx, sessionID, path) error` | Recursively removes directory | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.12 | Handle non-existent directory on remove | Returns ErrDirectoryNotFound | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** All directory operations work correctly.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.11 — Stat and Metadata Operations\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.11.1 | Implement `Stat(ctx, sessionID, path) (*FileInfo, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.2 | Return metadata for files | FileInfo has Name, Size, Type=File, timestamps | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.3 | Return metadata for directories | FileInfo has Name, Type=Directory | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.4 | Handle non-existent paths | Returns ErrFileNotFound or ErrDirectoryNotFound | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.5 | Include symlink information | IsSymlink and LinkTarget populated | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Stat returns correct metadata for files and directories.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.12 — Move and Copy Operations\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.12.1 | Implement `Move(ctx, sessionID, sourcePath, destPath) (*FileInfo, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.2 | Validate both source and destination paths | Invalid paths return error | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.3 | Handle non-existent source | Returns ErrFileNotFound or ErrDirectoryNotFound | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.4 | Execute move in sandbox | File/directory moved successfully | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.5 | Return FileInfo for destination | Info reflects new path | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.6 | Implement `Copy(ctx, sessionID, sourcePath, destPath) error` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.7 | Validate source and destination paths | Invalid paths return error | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.8 | Handle non-existent source | Returns ErrFileNotFound | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.9 | Execute copy in sandbox | File copied successfully | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.10 | Both files exist with identical content | Destination matches source | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Move and Copy operations work correctly.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.13 — Batch Operations\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.13.1 | Create `pkg/picod/file_batch.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.2 | Implement `BatchStat(ctx, sessionID, paths) (map[string]*FileInfo, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.3 | Return metadata for all existing files | Map contains FileInfo for each existing path | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.4 | Exclude non-existent files from result | Map only contains existing files | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.5 | Implement `BatchDelete(ctx, sessionID, paths) (*BatchResult, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.6 | Delete all specified files | Files removed from sandbox | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.7 | Return BatchResult with success/failure counts | SuccessCount and FailureCount correct | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.8 | Report partial failures in Failures map | Map contains errors for failed paths | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.9 | Implement `BatchCopy(ctx, sessionID, pairs) (*BatchResult, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.10 | Copy all files efficiently | BatchResult reflects all operations | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.11 | Handle partial failures in batch copy | Failures map contains errors | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.12 | Handle context cancellation during batch | Stops processing on cancellation | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** All batch operations work with partial failure handling.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.14 — File Watching\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.14.1 | Create `pkg/picod/file_watcher.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.2 | Implement `WatchDirectory(ctx, sessionID, path, opts) (*Watcher, <-chan FileEvent, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 1h |\n| 4.14.3 | Validate watching is enabled | Returns error if EnableFileWatching=false | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.4 | Validate max watchers limit | Returns error if MaxWatchers exceeded | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.5 | Create event channel | Channel returned correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.6 | Return Watcher handle with Stop method | Watcher has Stop() method | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.7 | Deliver FileCreated events on file creation | Event received when file created | 1h |\n| 4.14.8 | Deliver FileModified events on file modification | Event received when file modified | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.9 | Deliver FileDeleted events on file deletion | Event received when file deleted | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.10 | Deliver FileRenamed events on file rename | Event received when file renamed | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.11 | Support recursive watching | Subdirectory changes trigger events | 1h |\n| 4.14.12 | Support pattern filtering | Only matching paths trigger events | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.13 | Support event type filtering | Only selected event types delivered | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.14 | Implement Watcher.Stop() to close channel | Channel closed, resources released | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.15 | Handle context cancellation | Watcher stops on context done | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Directory watching works with all event types and options.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.15 — Sandbox Integration\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.15.1 | Create `pkg/picod/sandbox_file_client.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.15.2 | Define `SandboxFileClient` interface | Interface with all file operations | 0.5h |\n| 4.15.3 | Implement sandbox resolution by SessionID | Query store for sandbox endpoint | 0.5h |\n| 4.15.4 | Implement file read call to sandbox | Request sent to sandbox file API | 0.5h |\n| 4.15.5 | Implement file write call to sandbox | Request sent to sandbox file